Commentary Text: Akeal Hosein to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by Markram!! Akeal wins the battle!! He shows bravery to toss it up again, this one pitches slightly shorter and turns, not allowing Marsh to get under to slog. The Aussie batter goes for the big shot nevertheless, and gets a leading edge that goes high in the air. Markram runs back from extra cover, settles under and completes the take. Big, big wicket in the context of the game! Mitchell Marsh c Markram b Akeal Hosein 63(39) [4s-1 6s-6]

Commentary Text: Abhishek Sharma to Manish Pandey, out Stumped!! Lovely delivery. Spinner's delight. Pandey was charging out before Abhishek Sharma had even released, and the left-armer slowed his ball and kept it short. Beat Pandey with the turn on the outside edge, and he was pretty much halfway down the track before Klaasen completed the easiest of stumpings... But hang on, a check on whether Klaasen collected ahead of the stumps. Nope, all fine. Well behind the stumps, wonder what prompted a third umpire check? Manish Pandey st Klaasen b Abhishek Sharma 1(3)

Commentary Text: Markande to Philip Salt, out Caught&Bowled!! What a catch!! This was short on off again, Salt slaps it hard back in the direction of the bowler. Markande would have had milliseconds to adjust, and the ball was pretty low as well. But he gets both hands behind it and plucks out a stunning reflex catch of his own bowling. End of a superb fifty, a possible route back for SRH? Philip Salt c and b Markande 59(35) [4s-9]

Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Warner, out Bowled!! Bhuvi has struck gold! Warner throws his head back and walks off. He would have wanted to guide his side home v SRH. But is guilty of playing too far across the line to a ball that's not way too short and still swinging away. Miserly Bhuvneshwar keeps it just outside off stump and forces the error from Davey. Chop on and mute button on in Delhi. Warner b Bhuvneshwar 0(2)
